	<h2 class="title">Brighton &amp; Hove Governor Support&nbsp;</h2>

				<a name="SubTitle1"></a>
			
	<h4 class="plain">Learning Development Centre, Moulsecoomb</h4>

				<a name="BodyText1"></a>
			
		<span id="blacktext">
			&nbsp; 
<P>Brighton &amp; Hove Governor Support&nbsp;provides training and support for school governors and managers in Brighton and Hove, through a<A href="/site01.cfm?request=b1000330"> training programme</A>, governor newsletter, <A href="/site01.cfm?request=b1115355">school bulletins </A>and work with individual governing bodies. The section is involved in the recruitment and appointment of governors. It provides information about legislation relating to schools and practical information such as term dates.&nbsp; You can find out more information by going to the <A href="/site01.cfm?request=c1112861">contents page.</A>&nbsp; <A name=BodyText2></A>The Section works with groups such as the <A href="#network">Governors' Network </A>to consult on government regulations, LEA procedures and other issues relating to school governance and management and provide information and clarification on their implementation.</P>
<P><A name=SubTitle1></A>&nbsp;</P>Frequently Asked Questions<A name=BodyText3></A> 
<P><EM>How can I become a governor?To find out more about becoming a governor contact <STRONG>Janis Winkworth</STRONG> <STRONG>(01273) 293506 or Rose Wisdom (01273) 293507 or e.mail&nbsp; - <A href="mailto:Governor.Support@brighton-hove.gov.uk">Governor.Support@brighton-hove.gov.uk</A></STRONG>.&nbsp; to find out what is involved and how to apply.
<P><A name=TP></A><SPAN id=blacktext>&nbsp;
<P><STRONG>Training Programme</STRONG></P>
<P><STRONG>The Training Programme is issued&nbsp;each term. To obtain a copy please contact Geraldene Newman on (01273) 293595 or e.mail&nbsp; - <A href="mailto:governor.support@brighton-hove.gov.uk">governor.support@brighton-hove.gov.uk</A>
<P><STRONG><A name=network>The Governors' Network</A></STRONG></P>
<P><STRONG>The Governors' Network is open to all governors at schools in Brighton &amp; Hove. It meets once a term to discuss issues of interest to governors. The elected committee meets more often and undertake consultations on behalf of local governors. For details of the next meeting date contact Janis Winkworth&nbsp;on (01273) 293506.
